1. Input
    <form>
      <input type='', placeholder=''>   # set an input block, show the hint inside
      EX: <input name='username' type='text' placeholder='username'>
          <input name='password'type='password' placeholder='password'>
          <input type='submit'>
     </form>
   
2. Form
    where the form send data to?
      <form action:'http://wikipedia.org' method='GET'>
        so like this, we send data to wikipedia
    what HTTP method?
       if add the name='password', it will senf data to URL in action after submit with request
    
3. Labels
    <lable>username <input></lable>
    # put the label and input inside the lable tag
    another style is using for and id to connect each other!
    <label for='username'>username</label>
    <input id='username' type='text' placeholder='username'>
    
4. Validations
    add requried inside <input> to ask block to meet the type
    like if type is email, the input should be email type
   
5. Radio button and checkbox
    <input type='radio'>
    <input type='checkbox'>
    # radio button and checkbox button also can link with lables (for and id)
    # if set two or more radio as the same name, only one of them can be chosen
    # <button>CLICKS HERE</button> press button it will send data to somewhere,
    # but you need add value inside of input <input value='cats'>.
    
6. Dropdowns Meum
    <select name='color'><option value='RED'>red</option></select>
    # you can put how many options inside select you want.
    # give select a name, it will send the data too
    # if you want to send another data of option, add a value inside option

7. textarea
    <textarea rows='10' cols='20'></textarea>
    # a larger input area
